choices.text: with our income tax system, specifically the percentage payable as taxes on certain income levels such as the upper middle class to upper classes, such as selling online. When you are making more than $90,000.00 a year, the rate is 48% and much of this top rate income is taxed on even more modest income, such as interest earned from investments and retirement savings. I personally do not believe that this system is fair to individuals, such as consultant gardeners, in this part of the wealth spectrum, as the earnings from the business ventures offering personal services can end up being heavily taxed at high rates. This can put a cap on many excellent potential small business ventures, and has had a negative impact on employment, and the overall economy over the years. Thus it would appear that is may become a career limitation, in many cases, if income streams are generated too aggressively. Is there anyway, overtaxed small businesspeople can lower their tax burden and have more money to invest into their retirement savings, in the end, especially for canadians that the auxiumalry income from self employment should be included against retirement savings contributions, like it is in the usa system, for the self employed????
